cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.CE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses building high quality cloud applications and proposes a framework for predicting QoS ranking of cloud services. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses improving the QoS performance of cloud services through an optimal VM allocation policy. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses cloud services being invoked remotely over the internet. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as cloud computing is widely used in scientific computing and the paper discusses predicting QoS ranking for cloud services. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses improving the QoS performance of cloud services through an optimal VM allocation policy.
